{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013v2yypg7xd6hxKHK3owiP3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the parser stores `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` as the config value, not just the path. Now let's look at what the handler does:\n\n```go\nif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))\n```\n\nIt's trying to read a file with path `dir + file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` which obviously won't work. The handler needs to extract the path from the `file(\"...\")` wrapper.\n\nSimilarly for \"script\" config - it might also use `file(...)` syntax.\n\n\nI need to add logic to `handleAPIStepContent` that unwraps the `file(\"...\")` syntax before attempting to read the file path.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":549,"cache_read_input_tokens":39053,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":549},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f859d082-0f5e-4b4e-b172-aed8cb5e717f","uuid":"0aac7422-e0ae-4260-ab9a-db3c035e18e9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013v2yypg7xd6hxKHK3owiP3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug. The DSL parser stores prompt values as `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` (with the `file(...)` wrapper), but `handleAPIStepContent` uses the raw config value directly as a file path. It needs to extract the path from the `file(\"...\")` wrapper."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":549,"cache_read_input_tokens":39053,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":549},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f859d082-0f5e-4b4e-b172-aed8cb5e717f","uuid":"d98ff9c4-6bc6-4508-8735-9d839261f813"}
